      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Naturally occurring compounds called <i>terpenoids,</i> which we’ll discuss in <b>Section 27.5</b>, are biosynthesized by a pathway that involves loss of CO<sub>2</sub> from 3-phosphomevalonate 5-diphosphate to yield isopentenyl diphosphate. Use curved arrows to show the mechanism of this reaction.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBcmtXIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--70b39f46c5ebada4380d7428ecaa4a398f0003b0/OChem_20_EC_020.jpg\" alt=\"The reaction of 3-phosphomevalonate 5-diphosphate forms three products: isopentenyl diphosphate, carbon dioxide, and phosphate.\">\n",
